-- Chilean Stocks: Andina, Besalco and Soquimich Were Active
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-05-09T21:29:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-09/chilean-stocks-andina-besalco-and-soquimich-are-active.html
The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close in Santiago.  The  Ipsa index  retreated 0.6 percent to 4,492.75. The  MSCI
Chile (MXCL)  index fell 1.6 percent to 2,508.12.  Besalco SA (BESALCO)   snapped a three-day winning streak
and fell 1.2 percent to 975 pesos, the biggest drop in three
weeks. The Chilean construction company’s rating was cut to hold
from buy at Santiago-based brokerage Larrain Vial SA.  Embotelladora Andina SA (ANDINAB)   rose 1.9 percent to
2,700 pesos. Chile’s largest Coca-Cola bottler had its target
price increased to 2,760 pesos from 2,630 pesos and was
reiterated at neutral, the equivalent of a hold recommendation,
at local lender Banco de Credito & Inversiones.  Soc. Quimica & Minera de Chile SA  (SQM/B CC) dropped 0.7
percent to 27,718 pesos. The country’s largest fertilizer
producer declined as agricultural commodity prices amid concern
 Greece ’s political situation is threatening the global recovery.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
